  "text": "At follow-up from 2003 to 2007, digital non-stereoscopic 45°macular photographs of both eyes were taken with a Canon CR6-45NM non-mydriatic retinal camera. Retinal photographs were graded for AMD by two experienced graders, using \"OptoLite/OptoMize Pro\" software (Digital HealthCare Image Management Systems, Cambridge, UK), and classified according to the Clinical Classification of AMD [CITATION_1] . Quality control procedures for the photographs in the MCCS have been described elsewhere [CITATION_2] .",
